cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.PL

This paper focuses on performance optimization of deep learning frameworks, which is a key concern in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as parallelism is a key aspect of the paper. The paper also discusses the impact of design features on performance, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper proposes guidelines for performance tuning, which could be relevant to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
